#MentalHealthMatters #repost @kennethcolereal We know that post-Covid everybody in this country will be dealing with mental health related issues (if not them directly, certainly with someone they love). 

We at The Mental Health Coalition (MHC), are proud to launch an initiative that will ‚Äúchange culture‚Äù around the devastating stigma affecting millions living w mental health conditions.

Every day, an influential actor, athlete, or  influencer will go live on our MHC Instagram handle for an honest  conversation about how they handle their stress and if/how they support others through theirs. 

We know that the more people talk about mental health, and normalize the conversation, the greater impact on the related stigma that today prevents millions from speaking out and/or seeking help. 

A culture changing event w 31 inspiring segments, featuring; 
31 Advocates,
31 compelling Conversations &
31 Mental Health Clinicians
Over 31 Days. 
 
A little history -- in the past 18 months, MHC has formed a diverse coalition of 31 of the largest mental health service providers/organizations in the country. 
This coalition of nonprofits, together with its partners at Facebook/Instagram are hosting ‚ÄúEvery day in May‚Äù.

It is with heavy hearts that we‚Äôve made the difficult decision as a family to say goodbye to Keeping Up with the Kardashians.

After what will be 14 years, 20 seasons, hundreds of episodes and numerous spin-off shows, we are beyond grateful to all of you who‚Äôve watched us for all of these years ‚Äì through the good times, the bad times, the happiness, the tears, and the many relationships and children. Thank you to the thousands of individuals and businesses that have been a part of this experience and, most importantly, a very special thank you to Ryan Seacrest for believing in us, E! for being our partner, and our production team at Bunim/Murray, who‚Äôve spent countless hours documenting our lives. 

Our last season will air early next year in 2021. 

We are so beyond grateful to everyone who has watched and supported our family these past 14 incredible years. We will be forever in debt to everyone who played a role in shaping our careers and changing our lives forever. Thank you for joining us on this crazy ride!! 

We love you all. 

Kris x

Yesterday, we announced the launch of #AmericasFoodFund, a commitment to ensure that all Americans have reliable access to food, and support those most affected by this crisis. Thank you to everyone who has already supported. 
America‚Äôs Food Fund supports two incredible organizations, @FeedingAmerica and @WCKitchen, who are on the front lines of this rapid-response effort.

Congratulations to my beautiful, kind, amazing, talented, creative, giving and generous friend @anastasiasoare on your well-deserved Angel Award last night given to you by the Los Angeles Ballet. I am so proud of you and appreciate all you do for others. You are such an inspiration to so many, especially me!!! I love you!! #anastasiasoare #love #family @losangelesballet #repost @anastasiasoare „Éª„Éª„Éª
Last night, I was honored to be the Angel Award recipient at the Los Angeles Ballet‚Äôs annual gala. It was a beautiful evening filled with such talent and passion for the arts. 
Many people don‚Äôt know the special place ballet has in my heart. While growing up in Romania, I took lessons myself as a child. And though I wanted so badly to have access to glamorous Hollywood movies, instead ballets were aired every Sunday night. The weekly tradition was my greatest joy, and years later, the art of ballet became my pillar for perseverance ‚Äî even while building a brow empire. 
Needless to say, to be honored by the ballet was a moment for which I wanted my dearest friends in attendance. I asked @KrisJenner if she would be willing to introduce me, and I was thrilled when she agreed. Kris has one of the largest and most loving hearts, but I was still floored by her touching speech. 
Kris, you delivered an introduction filled with such love and warmth. I am so undeniably lucky to have friends like you willing to rise to the occasion and to stand by my side through moments like these that give life its sweetness.  Thank you @krisjenner üí´ @losangelesballet üí´ üì∏by @captureimaging
